      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Clarithromycin and simvastatin are known to interact, potentially increasing the risk of severe muscle damage and liver issues, so they should generally not be taken at the same time. You should wait at least four hours between your doses to allow your body to metabolize the antibiotics before starting your cholesterol medication. It is crucial to consult your prescribing doctor or pharmacist immediately to confirm the safest timing and potentially adjust your simvastatin dosage or switch medications.",
