      "content": "Do not rely on online advice, as spacing the doses by 12 hours is still risky because clarithromycin blocks the liver enzymes responsible for breaking down simvastatin for many hours after the antibiotic is taken. This interaction can lead to dangerous muscle breakdown and kidney failure, which is why it is medically required to switch to a different cholesterol medication instead of just waiting. Please call your doctor immediately to switch to a safer statin like pravastatin or rosuvastatin, as taking both together—even apart—is not safe.",
